</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64566953">ReactOS is the closest but it can't run a modern browser. With all the people left behind with Windows 7 machines and soon 10 we need a version of Windows that is not tied to Microsoft's arbitrary end of support schedules. Computers should last for decades not 10 years like Microsoft is trying to impose. We know all about Linux but people want Windows like UIs not Gnome, KDE or Mate. They want native apps not Wine. The fact that more people haven't invested in free Windows alternatives is one of the reasons why Microsoft can get away with telemetry and forced MS accounts. A free MacOS alternative for older Macs would be useful too, especially now Apple is obsoleting Intel Macs.</div>
	</div>

